raw_data.title: IBM/Rational Toolsmith II
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Two (2) years of technical experience which applies to supporting one or more of the IBM/Rational tools and or technologies.   Requires competence in installation and configuration of the Rational Suites and or ClearCase.                            Functional Responsibility:  Installs the Rational tools and configures user’s desktops based on Rational guidelines and project policies.              Minimum Education:  Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or related discipline.  A total of three (3) years supporting 1 or more projects may be substituted for the education requirement.

raw_data.title: IBM/Rational Subject Matter Expert III
raw_data.description: Minimum/General Experience:  Five (5) years of technical experience which applies to supporting one or more of the IBM/Rational tools and or technologies.   Requires competence installation and configuration of the Rational Suites and or ClearCase.  Requires competence in two of the following areas:               Rational ClearQuest Customization including schema modification and report format creation.               ClearCase VOB and View creation and management.              Required to be a Certified Rational consultant in two (2) or more of the IBM/Rational tools or technologies.              Requires competence in the design and configuration of an enterprise deployment of the suite of Rational tools.              Functional Responsibility:  Provides user support to project team members using the IBM/Rational tools.  Responsible for detailed customizations to the one or more of the Rational tools as well as integration of two ore more of the Rational tools.               Minimum Education:  Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science or related discipline.  A total of nine (9) years supporting 1 or more projects may be substituted for the education requirement.
